description: The Sub-Fund is an index-tracking UCITS passively managed. The Reference Currency of the Sub-Fund is the US Dollar (USD). The investment objective of the sub-fund is to reflect the performance of the Bloomberg Barclays Global Inflation-Linked 1-10 Year Index (the "Benchmark Index") denominated in USD and representative of the government local currency inflation linked debt from developed market countries – while minimising the volatility of the difference between the return of the Sub-Fund and the return of the Benchmark Index (the “Tracking Error”).
name: Amundi Global Government Inflation-Linked Bond 1-10Y UCITS ETF Dist
